title: About Me
text:
My goal is to be a Wildlife Biologist in my home state for the New York State Department of Environmental Conservation!



I received my Bachelors degree in Biology from the University at Albany and now I am pursuing my Masters in Wildlife Conservation and Biology at the University of New Hampshire.



Before coming to grad school, I worked for the Seneca Nation Environmental Protection Department as an Environmental Intern and then as the Climate Change Program Manager!
Thanks for checking out my web site!
